definitions.definition: One who works by the job (i.e. paid per individual piece of work) and/or recruits other people for such work.
An actor temporarily employed for a specific role , often in a touring company .
A promoter or broker of stocks for investment.
An intermediary who buys and sells merchandise.

subdefinitions.definition: A type of intermediary in the apparel industry, as well as others, who buys excess merchandise from brand owners and manufacturers, and sells to retailers at prices that are 20-70% below wholesale.
A market maker on the stock exchange ; a stockjobber .

definitions.definition: A performer whose primary role is to lose to established talent.
A thing ( often used in a vague way to refer to something the name of which one cannot recall ).

main_definition: ( archaic ) One who works by the job (i.e. paid per individual piece of work) and/or recruits other people for such work. [19th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( theater ) An actor temporarily employed for a specific role , often in a touring company .
( obsolete , UK , finance ) A promoter or broker of stocks for investment.
An intermediary who buys and sells merchandise.
( professional wrestling slang ) A performer whose primary role is to lose to established talent.
( slang ) A thing ( often used in a vague way to refer to something the name of which one cannot recall ).
